    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Please tell me how you will be able to get the rows for US/Eastern 09:00am, if the dataframe time zone is set to Europe/Berlin for example without actually accounting for time difference?\r\n\r\nYou are simply creating dependency between the code that prepared the dataframe, and the code that consumes the dataframe. If you add timezone parameter to these functions you may explicitly specify which time you are talking about. Time without a timezone doesn't represent a universal point in time."
